@page "/posts/intro"

<PageTitle>intro — c-t-fallon</PageTitle>

<div class="post">
    <div class="post-meta">
        <span class="post-date">2026-04-30</span>
        <span class="post-kind">post</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="post-title">intro</h1>

    <div class="post-body">
        <p>
            I'm a structural engineer who writes software. Most of what I do professionally involves
            concrete and steel — detailing connections, checking loads, coordinating with fabricators.
            On the side I build tools, mostly to solve problems I run into at work or just because
            something seemed interesting to figure out.
        </p>
        <p>
            This site is a place to put that stuff. Some of it will be interactive tools, some of it
            will be writing about things I've been working through. It's not a portfolio and it's not
            a blog in any disciplined sense — more of a running record of what I've been making.
        </p>
        <p>
            The tools tend to sit at the intersection of structural engineering and software: things
            that are annoying to do by hand, or where I wanted to understand the math well enough to
            implement it myself. The writing will probably follow a similar pattern.
        </p>
        <p>
            If something here is useful to you, that's a bonus.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
